## Seating depth comfort ##

Seating depth comfort in a living room depends on how the sofa supports the back and legs during use. A standard comfortable seat depth typically ranges from about 50 to 60 cm for upright sitting, while deeper seats around 60 to 70 cm offer a more relaxed, lounge-style experience. The right depth should allow the userâ€™s feet to rest flat on the floor with proper back support. Selecting appropriate seating depth enhances posture, reduces fatigue, and improves overall comfort.